  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0ddd\u0da8\u0dcf\u0db7\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d82\u0d9c\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d8a\u0dba\u0dda \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President Gotabaya will not go to Singapore yesterday",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Foreign media reported that President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa did not take off from Singapore flight SK 437 which was supposed to go from Male to Singapore.",
        "The media stated that due to security reasons, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, Mrs. Loma Rajapaksa and the two bodyguards did not leave the plane.",
        "Maldivian media reported that they are negotiating to get a private plane for President Gotabaya Rajapaksa to leave for Singapore.",
        "As President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa was scheduled to leave for Singapore yesterday (13) at 11.25 PM Maldives time, the foreign media further stated that strict security was provided at Velena International Airport in Maldives and that after going to Singapore, he may send his resignation to the Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka, Mr. Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena. said"
      ],
